  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\n\r\nCurrently, trinity is not correctly handling `KeyboardInterrupt` for asyncio loop based processes.  \r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n\r\nFill this in if you know how to fix it.\r\n\r\nWe need to make use of the [`asyncio.loop.add_signal_handler`](https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio-eventloop.html#asyncio.AbstractEventLoop.add_signal_handler) API to do proper keyboard interrupt signal handling.",
